An $alpha$-particle decay is modeled using a quantum wave packet. When does the quantum description of the wave packet spread significantly compared to the classical particle trajectory?
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
When $t >> tau = m sigma_x^2 / planck$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
When $t << tau$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
When $t = 0$
#pagebreak()
#set page(width: a_width, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
Never
